  "prompt": "Is money laundering considered an illegal practice?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered an illegal practice worldwide. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (often referred to as \"dirty money\") appear legitimate by passing it through a complex sequence of financial transactions, businesses, or other means. The purpose of money laundering is to conceal the illicit origin of the funds, making them appear as if they were earned through lawful activities.\n\nMoney laundering is illegal because it facilitates criminal activities such as drug trafficking, terrorism, fraud, corruption, and organized crime by allowing criminals to profit from their illegal actions while evading law enforcement. Most countries have strict anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations in place to detect, prevent, and prosecute these activities. Penalties for money laundering can include fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.",
